output.analysis:
Let me analyze this post according to the specified criteria:
1. Has CMF: No CMF number is present in the post.
2. Refers to candidate: Yes, explicitly mentions and supports Călin Georgescu, who is one of the presidential candidates (#11 on the official list).
3. Addresses wide population: Yes - It's a paid advertisement on Facebook and Instagram - Targets multiple counties - Reached between 9,000-9,999 impressions - Large estimated audience size (500,001-1,000,000)
4. Electoral objective: Yes - Direct statement of support ("Sustin Calin Georgescu!") - Makes political commentary about polling numbers - Clear intention to influence voters' opinions - Suggests potential censorship by other parties (PSD)
5. Journalism: No - This is clearly a promotional message, not journalistic content - Lacks objectivity and factual reporting - Contains personal opinion and political stance - No attempt at balanced reporting or information
Additional factors: - Timing: Posted and running during the period after presidential campaign ended - Geographic targeting: Focused on several Romanian counties - Significant reach through paid promotion

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: This constitutes electoral propaganda because: - Explicitly promotes a presidential candidate - Uses paid distribution channels - Has clear electoral objective - Targets wide audience - Running after campaign period ended
conclusion.message-for-police: Marian Ciofîcă, pentru incalcarea articolului 55 t) din Legea 370/2004, prin difuzarea unei reclame platite pe Facebook (ID postare: 1624012695133033) cu continut de propaganda electorala in favoarea candidatului Călin Georgescu, dupa incheierea perioadei de campanie electorala. Postarea, activa dupa ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024, contine mesaje directe de sustinere a candidatului ("Sustin Calin Georgescu!") si are un impact semnificativ, atingand intre 9.000 si 9.999 de afisari in mai multe judete, reprezentand o clara tentativa de influentare a alegatorilor in afara perioadei legale de campanie.
